TITLE: Viewing PDF Bytes in Hexadecimal Format
DESCRIPTION: Command for viewing bytes at a specific offset in a PDF file in hexadecimal format, providing a raw byte view for debugging.
SOURCE: https://github.com/Hopding/pdf-lib/blob/master/docs/CONTRIBUTING.md#2025-04-12_snippet_12

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
cat foo.pdf | tail -c +OFFSET | head -c NUM_BYTES | hexdump -e '6/1 " %02X" "\n"'
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Example of Viewing PDF Byte Range
DESCRIPTION: Example command that shows how to view 100 bytes from a PDF file starting at offset 560477.
SOURCE: https://github.com/Hopding/pdf-lib/blob/master/docs/CONTRIBUTING.md#2025-04-12_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
cat foo.pdf | tail -c +560477 | head -c 100
```

