TITLE: Drawing Text on a Page in pdf-lib v0.x.x (Old Method)
DESCRIPTION: Shows the deprecated method for drawing text on a PDF page in v0.x.x, which required creating a content stream, invoking operators, and registering the stream.
SOURCE: https://github.com/Hopding/pdf-lib/blob/master/docs/MIGRATION.md#2025-04-12_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const contentStream = pdfDoc.createContentStream(
  drawText(
    timesRomanFont.encodeText('Creating PDFs in JavaScript is awesome!'),
    {
      x: 50,
      y: 450,
      size: 15,
      font: 'TimesRoman',
      colorRgb: [0, 0.53, 0.71],
    },
  ),
);
page.addContentStreams(pdfDoc.register(contentStream));
```
